cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the training of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for training CNNs, which involves adding auxiliary supervision branches and utilizing probabilistic knowledge for regularization. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on image classification datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
